'''Sila''' (alternatively spelled '''Si'la''' or called '''Si'lat''') is a [[supernatural]] creature assigned to the [[jinn]] in [[Arabian]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Sílā {{!}} Arabian spirit |url=https://www.britannica.com/topic/sila-Arabian-spirit |website=Encyclopedia Britannica |language=en}}</ref> folklore. They are described as talented shapeshifters often appearing in human form and female.<ref>Patrick Hughes, Thomas Patrick Hughes ''Dictionary of Islam'' Asian Educational Services 1995 {{ISBN|978-8-120-60672-2}} page 135</ref> Accordingly they are said to seduce men, marry them or even give birth a child from a relationship between human and jinn.
== See also == * [[Succubus]] - A similar being in European and Jewish mythology
